    <!-- Help Screen -->
    <string name="help_title">Help</string>
    <string name="help_subtitle">Frequently asked questions</string>
    <string name="faq_q1">How do I make a reservation?</string>
    <string name="faq_a1">Go to \"My Reservations\" and press the floating \"+\" button. Select the date, start and end time, choose an available spot (green) and confirm. You need to have at least one vehicle registered to be able to reserve.</string>
    <string name="faq_q2">How far in advance can I reserve?</string>
    <string name="faq_a2">You can make reservations up to 7 days in advance.</string>
    <string name="faq_q3">How long can I reserve a spot for?</string>
    <string name="faq_a3">The maximum reservation time per session is 9 hours.</string>
    <string name="faq_q4">What types of spots are there?</string>
    <string name="faq_a4">The parking has 50 spots distributed into: normal spots, spots for electric vehicles (with charger), spots for motorcycles, and spots adapted for people with reduced mobility. Each spot is identified with its corresponding icon.</string>
    <string name="faq_q5">Can I see who has reserved a spot?</string>
    <string name="faq_a5">Yes, in the \"Check Parking\" section you can select a date and see the occupied spots. By clicking on an occupied spot you will see who reserved it and their license plate.</string>
    <string name="faq_q6">How do I add a vehicle?</string>
    <string name="faq_a6">Go to \"Profile &amp; Vehicles\" and press the \"Add Vehicle\" button. Select the vehicle type (car, electric, motorcycle or disabled) and enter the license plate. You must have at least one vehicle registered to be able to make reservations.</string>
    <string name="faq_q7">How do I report a problem?</string>
    <string name="faq_a7">Use the \"Report\" section of the menu. Select the type of problem (cleaning, damage, lighting, security or other), indicate the spot number if applicable, and describe the problem in as much detail as possible.</string>
    <string name="faq_q8">How do notifications work?</string>
    <string name="faq_a8">The app keeps you informed with notifications about your upcoming reservations, reminders and confirmations. You can see all your notifications by clicking on the bell icon in the top bar.</string>
    <string name="faq_q9">Can I cancel a reservation?</string>
    <string name="faq_a9">Yes, you can cancel your reservations from \"My Reservations\". Simply expand the reservation you want to cancel and press the delete button. Keep in mind that this action cannot be undone.</string>
    <string name="faq_q10">What if my email is not @lksnext.com?</string>
    <string name="faq_a10">Only employees with corporate @lksnext.com email can register in the system. If you need access and do not have this email, contact the facilities department.</string>
    <string name="faq_q11">What do the colors mean in the Check Parking view?</string>
    <string name="faq_a11">In the parking view, spots are shown in three colors:\n\n• Green = Available: no one has reserved the spot at that time.\n• Yellow = Your reservation: you have an active reservation in that spot.\n• Gray = Occupied: another user has reserved that spot.</string>
    <string name="faq_q12">Why do the occupied spots change when viewing today vs another day?</string>
    <string name="faq_a12">When you select today, only spots with an active reservation right now are shown as occupied. If a reservation starts later, the spot will appear free until that time. When you select a future day, all reservations scheduled for that day are shown, regardless of the time.</string>
    <string name="more_help_title">Need more help?</string>
    <string name="more_help_desc">Contact the facilities department at example@lksnext.com or call ext. 1234</string>

